The **EPF contribution** is 12% of (Basic + DA) from both employee and employer. However, the employer's 12% is split: 3.67% to EPF and 8.33% to EPS (Employee Pension Scheme, capped at ₹1,250/month). Employees can additionally contribute a **Voluntary Provident Fund (VPF)** above 12% to increase their EPF corpus while earning the same 8.25% interest.
